<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3467980>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Characters used in phylogeny. A. Batrachidea flavonotata Bolívar, 1887. B. Rehnidium omnivagum Grant, 1956. C. Tettigidea parradae Cadena-Castañeda & Cardona, 2015. D. Scaria rafaeli sp. nov. Habitus in lateral view to all specimens. Numbers indicate characters and states used in the cladistics analysis." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3467980/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3467982>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Characters used in phylogeny. A. Scaria ferruginea Hancock, 1909 (habitus in dorsal view). B. Apex of pronotum in dorsal view of B. flavonotata. C–F. Head and pronotum in lateral view: C. S. ferruginea. D. T. parradae. E. S. laeta. F. S. producta. G and H. Fore and mid legs respectively of S. rafaeli. I. Hind femur of S. producta. J–M. Tegmina: J. S. laeta. K. S. granti sp. nov. L. S. jonasi sp. nov. M. S. ferruginea. Numbers indicate characters and states used in the cladistics analysis." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3467982/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

